
rpdf extracts text and layout from PDF documents, using pdftohtml and
OCRopus.

version 0.2 (2010-04-04)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLATION
---------------------------------------------------------------------

rpdf requires slightly modified versions of specifc OCRopus and
pdftohtml releases, which are included. To install pdftohtml:

cd pdftohtml
make
cd ..

To install ocropus, you need a few packages -- jam, libtiff-dev
libjpeg-dev, libpng-dev. E.g. on Debian-based systems:

sudo apt-get install jam libtiff-dev libjpeg-dev libpng12-dev
cd ocropus/iulib


cd ocropus/tesseract-2.03/
./configure
make
cd ..
./configure
jam
cd ..

Check the instructions in the relevant sub-directory if you run into
problems.

rpdf also needs ghostscript, which should be in every package manager:

sudo apt-get install ghostscript
whereis gs

If gs is not in /usr/bin/gs, adjust the path at the top of the rpdf
file.











---------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
---------------------------------------------------------------------

rpdf [-d int] [-p int] file.pdf

 -d int : debug level
 -p int : max. number of pages to parse

If -p is not specified, what happens depends on whether rpdf can use
pdftohtml or has to fall back on OCR. With pdftohtml, it will parse
all; with OCRopus it will parse 1-3 pages depending on the length of
the pdf document. (OCRopus is slow: expect 10-20 seconds per page.)

